A Day of Thanks at the MGV in Dinker
It was the 165th Stiftungsfest had invited to the MGV "Friedrich Wilhelm Dinker" this year and 52 guests active singers and their wives were happy to come.
In the club house restaurant "Witteborg" in Dinker all the harmonious coexistence enjoyed all about the music.
Traditionally, the foundation is solid, the most suitable festivity to make distinctions.
About the special award "Singer of the Year" was pleased this time secretary Rolf Wagener.
"You have not only a lot written for us, but have also turned so many round for us, this is our big thank you," said the chairman of the choir Erich Schlotmann.
The awards for participation in performances and rehearsals by Aktivitätssträußchen went this year to the choir director Dieter Schulze with 44 entries, followed by the honorary chairman Horst Pier Ribbert, the Chairman himself, and last year's "Singer of the Year" Friedrich Winkler with 42 participations.
Fifth grade took Wart Artur Brückner.
A particularly thank the Executive Board reported to the team of club hostess In Pier Ribbert, which had once again conjured up a top-class menu and Gerda Pier Ribbert for the table decorations.
The MGV "Friedrich Wilhelm" meets for its regular choir rehearsals on Tuesdays at 19.45 clock in the club house.
"New sangesfreudige voices always are welcome," said Schlotmann.
